#text=I found myself in my youth in a precarious and annoying position .
#text=Not only did I live in the very rough part of town with theives , drug dealers , and crack addicts , but I was without reliable transportation .
#text=I did , however , have enough money for bus fare .
#text=As the job search continued I found an oportunity on the other side of town working for Subway .
#text=The characters on the bus were generally normal people but there were always a few outliers that were a bit intimidating .
#text=Most of these reeked of alcohol and insanity .
#text=I usually did n't talk to too many people on the bus , just kept to myself .
#text=I would go to the transfer spot in downtown , and switch to the bus that would take me to my final location at Subway .
